You are given an integer $a$ (1 ≤ $a$ ≤ 10<sup>18</sup>). Find two integers $l$ and $r$ (1 ≤ $l$ ≤ $r$ < 10<sup>200</sup>) such that the following code will result in a value less than or equal to 0:

```
ans = solve(l, r) % a;
if (ans <= 0)
  ans += a;
```

where `solve(l, r)` calculates the sum of the digits of all integers from $l$ to $r$ (inclusive). 

It is guaranteed that a solution exists.
